Class ReportPrintService

java.lang.Object
services.subservices.ReportPrintService
All Implemented Interfaces:
IReportPrintService
public class ReportPrintService extends Object implements IReportPrintService
Service class responsible for generating detailed reports on booked project applications. Reports can be filtered by applicant attributes such as flat type, marital status, and age. The report displays information such as applicant name, age, marital status, and project/flat details.

    • printReport

      public String printReport(Scanner sc, BTOProject project)
      Generates a report of applicants who have successfully booked a flat in the specified BTO project. The report is generated after applying user-specified filters such as flat type, marital status, and age.
      Specified by:
      printReport in interface IReportPrintService
      Parameters:
      sc - Scanner for user input
      project - The BTOProject object for which the report is generated
      Returns:
      A formatted string containing the filtered applicant report, or null if no matching applicants are found

    • filterReportContent

      public Map<Applicant,ProjectApplication> filterReportContent(Scanner sc, Map<Applicant,ProjectApplication> applicantsAndApplication)
      Applies user-selected filters to a given map of applicants and their project applications. The following filters can be applied: - Flat type: TWO_ROOM or THREE_ROOM - Marital status: SINGLE or MARRIED - Age: either a specific value or a range (minimum and maximum)
      Specified by:
      filterReportContent in interface IReportPrintService
      Parameters:
      sc - Scanner for user input
      applicantsAndApplication - A map of applicants and their project applications
      Returns:
      A filtered version of the original map based on the selected filter criteria
